  <Subject Subject_ID="300038208">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300038131</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>chairs by function [300038131], chairs (furniture forms) [300037772], single seating furniture [300037771], seating furniture [300037769], furniture by form or function [300048628], furniture [300037680], furnishings by form or function [300037342], furnishings (works) [300037336], Furnishings (hierarchy name) [300037335], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Term generally applied to a variety of chairs with adjustable back heights and sometimes adjustable or revolving seats intended for use while playing a musical instrument. Use "music stools" for similar seating with a revolving or adjustable seat but no back and intended for use while playing the piano or other musical instruments.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Término aplicado generalmente a una variedad de sillas con respaldos de altura regulables y algunas veces asientos regulables o giratorios pensados para usarse mientras se toca un instrumento musical. Use "taburete de músico” para asientos parecidos con un asiento giratorio o regulable, pero sin respaldo pensados para usarse mientras se toca el piano u otros instrumentos musicales.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Benaming die meestal van toepassing is op verschillende soorten stoelen met een verstelbare rugleuning en soms ook een verstelbare of roterende zitting die tijdens het spelen op een muziekinstrument wordt gebruikt. Gebruik 'muziekkruk' voor soortgelijke stoelen met roterende of verstelbare zitting zonder rugleuning die zijn bedoeld voor gebruik tijdens het spelen van de piano of andere muziekinstrumenten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>此一詞彙通常是指各式各樣可調整椅背高度的椅子，部份的椅座亦可調整或可旋轉，可在演奏樂器時使用。若是指稱有著可旋轉或者是可調整的座位但沒有椅背，且是在彈奏鋼琴或其它樂器時使用的類似椅子，請用「音樂凳」一詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Der Begriff bezieht sich im Allgemeinen auf verschiedene Varianten eines Stuhls mit höhenverstellbarer Rückenlehne und manchmal auch verstellbarem oder drehbarem Sitz, der zum Gebrauch beim Spielen eines Instrumentes bestimmt ist. Siehe „Musikhocker“ für eine ähnliche Sitzgelegenheit mit drehbarer oder verstellbarer Sitzfläche, jedoch ohne Rückenlehne, die zum Klavierspielen oder zum Spielen eines anderen Instrumentes gedacht ist.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
